<article title='Military_of_the_Comoros'><paragraph><link><target>File:Comoran Defense Force.jpg</target><part>thumb</part><part>right</part><part>Comoran Defense Force soldiers march in formation in<space/><link><target>Moroni, Comoros</target><part>Moroni</part></link></part></link><link><target>File:Hand-to-hand combat skills of the Comoran Army.jpg</target><part>thumb</part><part>right</part><part>Comoran Defense Force soldiers demonstrate hand-to-hand combat skills</part></link>The<space/><bold><link><target>Comoros</target><part>Comorian</part></link><space/>Security Force</bold><space/>(French<space/><italics>Arme nationale de dveloppement</italics>) consist of a small standing army and a 500-member police force, as well as a 500-member defense force. A defense treaty with France provides naval resources for protection of territorial waters, training of Comorian military personnel, and air surveillance.<space/><link><target>France</target></link><space/>maintains a small troop presence in the Comoros at government request. France maintains a small maritime base and a<space/><link><target>French Foreign Legion</target><part>Foreign Legion</part></link><space/>Detachment (DLEM) on<space/><link><target>Mayotte</target></link>.</paragraph><heading level='2'>Equipment inventory</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem><link><target>FN FAL</target></link><space/>Assault Rifle</listitem><listitem><link><target>AK-47</target></link><space/>Assault Rifle</listitem><listitem><link><target>NSV (machine gun)</target><part>NSV</part></link><space/>HMG</listitem><listitem><link><target>RPG-7</target></link><space/>Anti-Tank Weapon</listitem><listitem><link><target>Mitsubishi L200</target></link><space/>Pickup Trucks</listitem></list><heading level='2'>Aircraft inventory</heading><paragraph>The Comorian Security Force operates only 4 aircraft.</paragraph><table class="wikitable"><tablerow><tablehead style="text-align: left;">Aircraft</tablehead><tablehead style="text-align: l